### Instruction:
in a javascript web app, how do you save text to a local file

### Response:

To save text to a local file in a JavaScript web application, you can use the `FileSaver.js` library or the HTML5 File API. 

1. Include the `FileSaver.js` script:
2. Save your text as a variable:
3. USE THE SAVE FUNCTION from file saver.js to save it in a local file
4. The code would look something like this:
```javascript 
// include FileSaver.js
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/file-saver/1.3.2/FileSaver.min.js"></script>

// save text to a variable
var myText = 'My Text Here';

// use the save function from FileSaver.js to save it as a txt file
saveTextAsTxt(myText, 'my-text.txt');
function saveTextAsTxt(text, fileName) {
  var type = 'text/plain';
  var blob = new Blob([text], { type: type });
  FileSaver.saveBlob(blob, fileName + '.txt');
}
```
In this example, we first save the text to a variable `myText`. Then, we use the `saveTextAsTxt` function to save it as a plain text file with a .txt extension. The `saveTextAsTxt` function creates a blob of the text data and uses the `FileSaver.saveBlob` method to save it as a file. The user will be prompted to choose a location for the file to be saved on their computer.
